article.headline: UC Davis 83, Cal Poly-SLO 63
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- Dominic Calegari scored 20 points on 8-for-10 shooting to lead UC Davis to an 83-63 victory over Cal Poly San Luis Obispo on Thursday night. Joe Harden had 19 points and eight rebounds, Todd Lowenthal scored 11 points and Mark Payne added 10 points and seven assists for the Aggies (9-12, 5-4 Big West). Lorenzo Keeler scored 30 points and made all 11 of his free throws for the Mustangs (8-13, 5-4). Keeler also sank five 3-point shots. The Aggies led by as many as 28 points, at 68-40, with 6:51 remaining in the game. Keeler scored the Mustangs' first 12 points to open the second half and didn't get a contribution from another teammate until Kyle Odister made a basket at the 10:13 mark. Calegari had 12 points and the Aggies made 9 of 10 free throws to lead 35-24 at intermission.
